After nine Major appearances, team&nbsp;Astralis managed their first victory&nbsp;at a&nbsp;Major&nbsp;this weekend at the ELEAGUE Major in Atlanta. The Danish team under coach Danny zonic S rensen was able to beat Polish team Virtus.Pro in three maps with 2:1 (12:16, 16:14, 16:14) and took home the first place prize of&nbsp;$500,000.After a disappointing group stage with only one win in four games, mousesports was out of the ELEAGUE Major.&nbsp;The German team reacted right away to its early exit and replaced&nbsp;Chris chrisJ de Jong with former mousesports player Tom "oskar"&nbsp; astn .Make sure to check out our eSports channel in YouTube for more.